Title: Software Quality Engineer II
Job_Description:
Position Summary:
The Software Quality Engineer II is a mid-level technical position requiring previous experience in software testing. Must be able to work with the development team to support project activities; write and execute a test plan; and have some previous experience with automated testing tools. Must be self-motivated and able to work in a fast-paced, challenging environment. The Software Quality Engineer II will collaborate with a team of skilled Software Engineers and Product Managers to develop and translate business goals into high quality, reliable and scalable technology. The Software Quality Engineer II will be part of a team that will deliver faster and set a high-quality bar and invest the time and commitment to automating tests. This position requires an individual who is creative, team-oriented, a quick learner and driven to produce results

Title: Software Quality Engineer II
Job_Description: Position Summary: The Software Quality Engineer II is a mid-level technical position requiring previous experience in software testing. Must be able to work with the development team to support project activities; write and execute a test plan; and have some previous experience with automated testing tools. Must be self-motivated and able to work in a fast-paced, challenging environment. The Software Quality Engineer II will collaborate with a team of skilled Software Engineers and Product Managers to develop and translate business goals into high quality, reliable and scalable technology. The Software Quality Engineer II will be part of a team that will deliver faster and set a high-quality bar and invest the time and commitment to automating tests. This position requires an individual who is creative, team-oriented, a quick learner and driven to produce results Position Responsibilities- Other duties may be assigned: Organize test efforts by establishing test criteria and test environments. Develop and execute test plans, identify defects and report findings to development team and management. Create test cases and test plans, employing automated test tools whenever possible. Actively participate in Agile ceremonies. Provide training and support to Customer Service on all new end-user products and utilities that are released. Develop manual and automated tests, enhance and expansion of the current Test Automation Infrastructure Support and test release deployments to QA, Staging and Production environments. Design, develop and maintain test automation tools/frameworks (e.g. Selenium WebDriver, Jenkins, SOAPUI, QAF, JIRA, Gherkins, TestNG, JMeter etc.). Position Requirements: Bachelor’s degree (BA, BS) in Computer Science or related computer/engineering field, or equivalent. 2-4 years’ of demonstrated experience in software development or software testing and quality assurance (QA) activities (automation experience strongly preferred). Well-versed in all testing methodologies (black box, white box, system, functional, exploratory and automated testing). Experience in creating and documenting test plan and test case scenarios and processes. Strong analytical skills, strong judgment and ability to understand complex business problems quickly. Familiar with SQL is desired. Experience in Agile/Scrum, JIRA or any other agile management or bug tracking tools. Experience with testing tools, preferred are Selenium/QAF/JMeter. Working knowledge of Java or C# or any object-oriented language. Ability to rapidly learn new technologies based on business needs. Excellent written and oral communication skills.

AutoZoners have a contagious work ethic; including a high sense of urgency to resolve issues quickly, creatively and efficiently. We also expect a high sense of responsibility and the ability to influence others. As an expert in your field, we expect you to:
Ensure that sites and systems continuously and consistently run smoothly, optimally, efficiently and reliably

Title: Systems Engineer (Supply Chain Full Stack Developer)
Job_Description:
Summary:
AutoZone is actively searching for an engineer who can think on their feet, work in vintage and cutting-edge technologies, all while helping a fast-paced growing business continue to expand. We focus on growing our engineers through training and helping them connect how their contributions directly make an impact to the business.
As a Store Systems Engineer, you’ll step into a success story of listening to customers and delivering the value of making it easier for commercial businesses to buy from AutoZone. You will collaborate with engineers from diverse backgrounds and cultures. There will be both opportunities to mentor and be mentored. Each deliverable we work on creates a story that can be connected to the value the team and you personally contributed to help grow the business. AutoZone has a strong culture where we value each other and focus on how to take care of our customers.

Data Scientist

At AutoZone, we rely on insightful data to power our systems and solutions. We’re seeking an experienced data scientist to deliver that insight to us on a daily basis. Job_Description:

This key role in our Supply Chain department would develops statistical models to support ongoing replenishment programs. For both the US and Mexico, hub and feeder networks, DC, supply chain services and various business process re-engineering projects.

Key Responsibilities
Implements replenishment projects for US, Mexico, and Brazil stores and DCs.
Monitors existing replenishment systems and intervenes where necessary.
Develops models for transportation and other aspects of supply chain. Includes optimizing the delivery frequency to the stores and determining optimal replenishment source (DC, Hub, CD, & DSD).

Title: Senior Data Analyst
Job_Description:
Position Summary:
Responsible for the preparation of pro forma financial statements for prospective customers and customer profitability and sustainability analyses. Create, update, and maintain tools and processes to track and evaluate customer financial performance. Serve as a business partner / advisor based on customer data research and analysis. Provide recurring as well as ad hoc reporting as needed.

Job Responsibilities - Other duties may be assigned:
Collaborate with key decision makers within Finance and Operations during the preparation of customer pro forma financial statements

Title: Senior Data Analyst
Job_Description:
SUMMARY
Sr. Pricing Analysts must be self-starters, detail oriented, able to handle multiple tasks, be a team player and be technically proficient at Microsoft Excel. Sr. Pricing Analysts are internal consultants for the merchandising department. The position is responsible for supporting pricing integrity (price accuracy) and implementation across the entire pricing lifecycle including initial pricing, every day pricing, price tests and markdown/clearance pricing. This role is directly responsible for using data-driven analytics to develop insights to strengthen pricing strategy recommendations. The Sr. Pricing Analyst supports Category Management teams by data mining and presenting findings as they build merchandising strategies. The position requires strong math skills, as well as a demonstration of strong analysis skills with a keen sense of business acumen.
